text:
#sharethis would you like an endeared group  of yours to engage in conversation with me about girls and women??? let's talk. 
i did not know when writing #wecomeasgirlsweleaveaswomen this story would be read & used as a tool to strengthen a heightened discussion about #girls & #womanhood. i have conversed with groups of women, here i discuss with a co-ed group of high school seniors, soon, i will be having an intimate discussion with high school males only. and these men-to-be are currently reading the book before i arrive so we can really get down to business! girls are not the only ones who need to understand their complex routes to maturity-#boys and #men benefit from being made aware, too. and now. less #metoo experiences for our future when boys are taught early how to fully respect women and girls. #seriousbusiness #startthediscussionnow #read #everyone @amazon

amazing news! as we all know, there have been many consequences of the #metoo movement worldwide. a recent study says that it may have actually contributed to reducing the stigma of sexual assault and similar types of abuse and harassment (based on a huge increase in related online searches), leading to more people seeking help and speaking out. this is a huge step forward for survivors. we have to keep speaking out and getting help. it's important to remember #youarenotalone 'the number of google searches related to sexual harassment or assault almost doubled as a result of the metoo movement, a study says.

the researchers said the results ‚Äúsuggest that metoo may have reduced the stigma of sexual harassment and/or assault as more seek help‚Äù.' read more at https://bit.ly/2epyxnf

text:
i want to share my story. from the multiple incidents of sexual violence, abuse, catcalling, eve-teasing - this is the most recent.

i am a solo traveller and i blog about my travels. i want to present a true picture of my travels and not just insta-worthy glam shots that would make the world jealous of me. this might not be the most life-shattering stalking incident but every girl knows the fear and anxiety of something like this because in the moment, we don't know if we'll get out of it unscathed.

so, this happened a year ago on my solo trip to pondicherry. while walking to the promenade on my first day in pondicherry, i noticed two men following me. i halted at a distance to substantiate my doubts. i wanted to be wrong. to my dismay, i wasn‚Äôt and they walked past me only to stand at a distance and wait for me to take the lead once again. i did and walked towards a crossing and stopped again to see where they‚Äôre going. they had probably seen my phone from behind and the google maps i was using, knew where i was headed, and so they took the calculated right. now, i was in a fix because that‚Äôs was i was headed. nevertheless, i took the left.

and thank god for museums! i quickly went in to get rid of my stalkers and spent about 40 minutes there ‚Äì coming out relatively relieved and a little more informed.
.
.
under section 354d indian penal code 1860 (ipc), any man who follows a woman and contacts, or attempts to contact such woman to foster personal interaction repeatedly despite a clear indication of disinterest by such woman commits the offence of stalking.

stalking is punishable on first conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and also with a fine.  on a second or subsequent conviction, stalking is punishable with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to five years and is also liable to a fine.
.
.
#metoo #standagainstharassment #reclaimthestreets #fightsexualharassment #endviolenceagainstwomen #standup4humanrights #timesup #humanrights #unwomen #unwomenindia

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
- "take a good look at the 33rd! edition of the #economist telling you in your face the state of the staged world in the upcoming episode of this ritualistic reality show that we have all unwillingly taken part in.
what does a stork usually carry in a bag? yeah, a baby...only this time the "product" has a barcode and a serial number on it as it is shipped from a supposed poor region (poor weirdo ghandi) of the world to the western land of the electric cars...someone should get on that serial number to decode it...and that vitruvian man with a night vision/virtual reality gear on...
‚Ä¢
all the satanic mirrored spells aside, "putin's pipelines" is written right above the depiction of the four horsemen of the apocalypse to come at the end of the world symbolizing conquest, war, famine, and plague/death...
‚Ä¢
i don't even wanna talk about the baseball, the "cell"phone, that hemp leaf and that fucking scale with 4=5 people on each side, 2+2=5 concept from 1984 programming written by a bbc whore of a mason with a fake name george whorewell...
‚Ä¢ 
there is a ton of symbolism, like the one-eyed black and white panda (china) sitting between putin-trump, the duality of the two voting boxes representing the fake political systems with south african and indian flags (with british ties that claimed independence) on them as opposed to that brexit bulldog, the pinocchio with an arrow on his face, the indian elephant tusk going up like a chart maybe representing the booming economy/tech of india, all those written headlines up there with as clear as daylight numeralogy attached to these letters which i can't even wanna start looking into anymore, the #metoo tattoo, that amarillo that symbolizes protection and boundaries with its protective shell reminding us to protect ourselves and a lot more hidden layers of esoteric meanings and geometry behind this...
‚Ä¢
many regards to my brother @loong_distance for exchanging ideas and decoding techniques...love how a healthy mind thinks..."
‚Ä¢
p.s. i dunno who are the two bitches at the bottom, i can't make anything out of ghandi with that salt-making device and can't read what's written above that elephant
.

text:
10 reasons why it pays to be a feminist

manny people think feminism is a dirty word reserved for angry women with armpit hair. whether you take this stance or believe that it should be shouted in the streets and celebrated as the equality amongst sexes it stands for, there are multiple reasons why it pays to be a feminist. male or female, feminism bridges the gap, and liberates all people from tainted beliefs and false narratives. men are expected to act a certain way, and women are expected to do the same. meanwhile, we are all stuck pointing fingers and accusing one another when all we need to do is open the floor to conversation on acceptance and understanding. shattering false narratives and building new ones for the benefit of all is what it's all about. we are all equal‚Äîregardless of our sex, gender, or race. failing to recognize this is what has gotten us in a lot of the trouble we experience today.

text:
2018 flashback :
kontroversi terbesar bollywood di tahun 2018 üòØ

bollywood terganggu oleh beberapa kontroversi tahun ini, yang memiliki efek buruk selama berbulan-bulan. sementara film-film seperti padmaavat dan manmarziyaan harus menderita dahulu sebelum mendapat rilisnya, bintang-bintang seperti sidharth malhotra dan kangana ranaut harus mengeluarkan klarifikasi atas penyataannya. 
1. gerakan me too
mantan aktris tanushree dutta dan aktor nana patekar memulai kasus berkepanjangan ini. tanushree menuduh nana telah melakukan pelanggaran seksual selama syuting film horn ok pleassss (2008). atas kejadian ini, membuka suara dna menyeret beberapa yokoh bollywood atas kasus yang sama. tuduhan terhadap pembuat film vikas bahl yang menyebabkan spanduk produksi phantom films dibubarkan. aktor alok nath juga dituduh melakukan pemerkosaan oleh seorang penulis-produser tv. sutradara sajid khan harus keluar dari pengarahan film housefull 4, dan beberapa nama tokoh besar lainnya di bollywood.

2. padmaavat
perilisan film sanjay lela bhansali, padmaavat telah diliputi oleh protes besar. poster dari perangkat padmaavat telah dirusak pada bulan desember 2017 dan mengakibatkan penundaan rilis hingga januari 2018. masalah yang dimulai pada akhir 2017 merebak hingga 2018. beberapa kelompok rajput termasuk karni sena memprotes, merusak properti film, dan bahkan mengeluarkan ancaman kepada sanjay leela bhansali dan aktris utama deepika padukone. mereka mengklaim bahwa padmaavat menggambarkan ratu rajput padmavati dalam cahaya yang buruk. sementara beberapa negara melarang film tersebut, mahkamah agung menolak sebuah petisi untuk perilisannya.

rilis yang dijadwalkan pada 1 desember 2017 dengan judul 'padmavati' ditunda di india. akhirnya tiba pada tanggal 25 januari 2018, dengan judul yang berubah menjadi 'padmaavat', dengan beberapa potongan adegan. film ini akhirnya memecahkan beberapa rekor box office setelah dirilis.

3. sidharth malhotra - bhojpuri
kontroversi sidharth malhotra dan neetu chandra telah menuai perhatian publik. neetu chandra telah menampar keras sidharth malhotra karena...(selengkapnya baca difacebook) üòâ

#indianexpress
#metoo
#padman
@padmaavat
#bhojpuri

text:
i am a feminist. i say this not because i think women are better than men or because i hate men, i don‚Äôt. i simply believe in gender equality.
the cambridge english dictionary gives the definition of feminism as "the belief that women should be allowed the same rights, power, and opportunities as men and be treated in the same way." more simply put; the idea that men and women should be treated equally. if you believe in gender equality, you therefore are by definition, a feminist. considering i can‚Äôt think of a valid reason as to why someone would not believe in gender equality, i undoubtedly believe that by these grounds, everyone should be a feminist. whether you actively involve yourself in the modern feminist movement is a choice, but equal rights shouldn‚Äôt be, and never should have been a debate. obviously there are ingrained, biological differences between men and women and we are clearly not the same, however this does not mean that either gender should be treated with any less respect or fewer rights. i‚Äôll admit, the feminist movement has its flaws, but so does any movement, and there are varying degrees of extremity to the views held by those involved in and leading it. but this means we all have a choice; in what we believe and how far we believe it, and this choice is what makes feminism such a positive association

text:
to all the enslaved african womxn who fought for womxn's liberation 
during the 500 year period of enslavement
to all the indigenous womxn who fought/fight against colonisation & imperialism
to all the domestic laborers who fought/fight corporate-agenda-serving labor laws
to all the the lesbian, queer, trans womxn who died fighting for all of our freedom to love and embody ourselves & who we choose to be
to all the mothers, aunties, sisters, cousins, daughters, who fight against childhood sexual assault in our homes, workplaces, in our streets
to the founders of black lives matter and the womxn who shoulder the movement 
to the civil rights movement womxn
to the black arts movement womxn
to the mau mau and the ahosi 
to nanny and amanirenas
to the guerilla womxn
to the courageous womxn unnamed
to the warrior womxn untamed
to the outcast and rejects 
the ones who will not stay quiet 
the ones who are hated & feared by the patriarchs & misogynists 
to the ones abandoned by our families in favor of abusers
to the survivors, the ones who are not liked nor loved
because we say no, because we resist
because we have no master
because we refuse to fall-in-line
we are not accomplices nor are we complacent
to the dangerous ones 
to the butus, the ghetto ones, the untouchables, the ratchets, the unrespectables, the whores, the sluts
the hags, the witches, the shit-disturbers, the bitches 
to all of us with a purpose & a promise on this earth

today, after 27 years 
i confronted the pedophile
the child sexual abuser
the molester of little black girls 
and my little black girl inside felt the deep love she desperately needed
from me. i stood up for her, even while terrified
i spoke up for myself, even while feeling bullied
today i understood the meaning of self-love
closure is the beginning 
of a new chapter
ase ancestors
thank you for walking with me
there is no equality without womxn's equality 
a revolution is brewing
-d‚Äôbi young anitafrika

#blacklivesmatter #metoo #metoomovement #metoomovement2018 #wetoo

because we refuse to fall-in-line
we are not accomplices nor are we complacent
to the dangerous ones 
to the butus, the ghetto ones, the untouchables, the ratchets, the unrespectables, the whores, the sluts
the hags, the witches, the shit-disturbers, the bitches 
to all of us with a purpose & a promise on this earth

today, after 27 years 
i confronted the pedophile
the child sexual abuser
the molester of little black girls 
and my little black girl inside felt the deep love she desperately needed
from me. i stood up for her, even while terrified
i spoke up for myself, even while feeling bullied
today i understood the meaning of self-love
closure is the beginning 
of a new chapter
ase ancestors
thank you for walking with me
there is no equality without womxn's equality 
a revolution is brewing
-d‚Äôbi young anitafrika

#blacklivesmatter #metoo #metoomovement #metoomovement2018 #wetoo

text:
i would like to blame the holidays for missing my post on monday but, if i‚Äôm honest i have been under a major car of writers block. 
have you ever met a someone and just felt like you had to know them in anyway they‚Äôd let you? you know the feeling when you just crave someone? not even in an erotic way, just their mere company in the simplest of formats. maybe, that is the most intimate form of craving there is. 
but, what do i know? i‚Äôm just a gal hiding behind a typewriter.

text:
helpless and abused.
_
would you treat a #dog this way?
_
dairy‚Äôs dark secret
the typical dairy cow on a farm produces nearly 22,000 pounds of milk a year ‚Äì more than double¬≠ what its forebears did 40 years ago. they never graze; their hooves have rotted from standing in their own filth. their babies are taken away immediately, so the mom can produce milk. 
_
cows, like pigs, are social creatures; their babies are even more so. they nuzzle strangers, groan with pleasure when you pet them, and attach without complaint to callous minders. their sweetness gets them nowhere at auctions or at farms, however; the men and women working here smack them with boards and kick them in the haunches to move them forward. as one undercover investigator stated; ‚Äúso common,‚Äù ‚Äúsaw guys punch them, stick cattle prods in their eyes, bragging, ‚Äòi totally got her in the eyeball!‚Äô it‚Äôs what happens when you do this long enough. they‚Äôre not your fellow creatures, they‚Äôre just trouble.
_
then there's the baby...a calf that can‚Äôt get up. its velveteen eyes are wet but blank; he barely stirs when jostled by other calves. ‚Äúhe got sick and gave up,‚Äù and so it goes with farmers who gave up farming to become cruel jailers of their "stock.‚Äù it‚Äôs like they hate their own animals for having feelings.‚Äù
_
how can you possibly justify this for a glass of milk, a piece of cheese, a bowl of #icecream ?there are so many plant-based alternatives available. please choose wisely. will your choices be responsible for creating more victims?

text:
blast from the past. i found this with a few others in some boxes i am clearing out for mum before she moves and i leave for home to malta... photocopies of photo of me as found within my modelling portfolio ... me at 16 when i was a hopeful model. i still hate the way my lips sit in photos... my husband and i always have a laugh at my mouth in photos. i guess my parents encouraged me love for singing, dancing, writing and modelling to some extent and here is proof.
.
i wish i could talk to the 16 year old me and tell her to stay strong and tough, to take no shit and that being loved and adored is not a basic human need, only a myth to make girls feel needy and act passive to keep men in power and hold up the illusion that women are not an equal part of this world.
.
.
.
.

text:
today marks my 18 year hijab-aversary. wow. when i think back to what my life looked like when i chose to be the first and only person in my immediate family to wear the hijab and how that decision has defined me, my identity and my life since, i am in awe. i would have it no other way.
üßïüèΩ
making the decision to wear the hijab was harder than most would think, and not for the reasons many assume. i had to fight against my own family initially to wear it. they were afraid in part of what others would think and how i might be treated. what they did not realize however is how it would empower me to find my voice. in standing up for my decision to choose to wear the hijab to my family, i found the resolve i needed to defend my choice to strangers.
üßïüèΩ
no woman should ever be told how to dress or how not to dress. my hijab is an integral part of the woman i am and i wear it with an honour and pride i cannot even begin to describe.
üßïüèΩ
üì∏: @visual.fascination taken at the @cpact.ca annual meeting
üßïüèΩ

i‚Äôm too scared, i‚Äôm too scared

text:
this picture was 3 yrs ago.

i was sitting on the kitchen floor playing music for my daughter so she could dance.

i was also in the middle of a ptsd episode.

it's not easy to have come this far.

to live almost ptsd free.

it's a combination of so much work.

work that only made things far worse before they ever got better.

it was a combination of
energetic
akashic
physical
yogic
chakra
plant
soul retrieval 
and so much prayer.

when you add ptsd to hyper sensitive and sensory processing disorder it can make normal live unbearable.

but it can also make life very legit.üíñüíñüíñ we aren't all wired exactly the same.

we don't all need the same teachers.

we don't all need the same medicine.

long term suffering is unneccassary .

here for the renegades and the white wolves. i don't have all the fucking answers but i can definetly light the way.

text: one of my first modeling photos, as i was c. 19 or 20 and got started later than most models...as my fam was totally against it, for the most irrational reasons at the time, since they knew nothing about the industry and had a thinking style that did not set me up for success. that said, i pushed beyond the mysoginy working against a chance at a better life and to earn a great deal, by working full time as an electrical engineering assistant, while caving in to go to college, yet paying my own way, working full time, going to college part time, and driving hours to start modeling on days i could get off, until i got to ny. fighting ignorance and ego issues taught me tenacity, but cost me critical years to earn as a model and the impoverished thinking style i was raised with set me up to be vulnerable to predators in the business. though it cost me, i never caved into the predators and eventually paid the price by getting stalked out of the business and harassed by a few dishonorable personalities...and still i grew, and learned, and empowered myself and continue to overcome and become all i can be as a woman of strength in her convictions...now for the sake of showing others who may benefit what i learned to ease their path toward success and autonomy. üëç #metoo #metoomovement #timesup #autism #autismspeaks #tulsa #oklahoma #fashionfotoge #fashionfotog #fashionfotogevita #evita #model #photographer #writer #travelwriter #manager #actor #talent #wildlifephotographer #wildlife #fashionphotographer #runwaycoach #actingcoach #videographer #artdirector #copywriter #graphicdesign #advertising #musicphotographer #petportraits

text: ‚Äúon a very personal note, my mother, who passed when i was ten, from cancer, and without knowing i would lose, then find this letter only after i started modeling years later, taught me beauty in its whole truth and exhibition...her legacy for me was to articulate and illustrate it as a gift to lift others, and not to define myself as a token of beauty. though i never operated as though there are not so many other people in the world whose beauty, intellect, talent and accomplishments had or could, surpass mine any day of the week and still do often esteem others higher than self, as is the definition of true grace in my opinion...how truly beautiful was my mother, to gift this eternal wisdom to me, whose very essence was as the lilt of an american beauty, my favorite rose, by the way...fragile, delicate to the touch, yet vibrant and even potent in its depth of colour...that, by virtue of such, eminates a radiance with an impact that is no less than everlasting. that...and nothing less, is the true definition of beauty...it is...love in motion...as it should be ‚Äòin earth as it is in heaven.‚Äô‚Äù ‚Äúwalk in peace and love so we can show the way back home.‚Äù by evita e.  #metoo #metoomovement #timesup #autism #autismspeaks #tulsa #oklahoma #fashionfotoge #fashionfotog #fashionfotogevita #evita #model #photographer #writer #travelwriter #manager #actor #talent #wildlifephotographer #wildlife #fashionphotographer #runwaycoach #actingcoach #videographer #artdirector #copywriter #graphicdesign #advertising #musicphotographer #petportraits

text: this is one of my first fashion images of a girl in atlanta who looked a lot like sade, in person, though a bit less on camera. still, she had potential and had done some small acting parts, but was not someone who seemed motivated to do much more as we chatted in general. and, that is one of the reasons it took me years to consider managing, or even being a booker. because, when i would help other model friends arrange their ‚Äúbooks‚Äù or teach them a better walk, i still could not help them find the tenacity in themselves the industry requires, and some even lacked the level of integrity one would hope for in a friend, or from a potential business perspective...such as one who, like my ex, would take my ideas and present them as her own. but, things happen the way they do and years later i feel much more seasoned or better equipped to guide talent, on many levels of the industry, with a strong desire to see good people flourish! - as well as, more polished in my own artistry that continues to develop too, behind the camera, etc. so, the take away is if i present a model, or talent, with the knowledge or opportunity to get to the next level and they do not take it, then it is their choice and managing is still something that interests me as an ornament on tree of my emerging renaissance...and i look forward to avenues to exercise my skills and interests; especially, when they culminate in win-wins! ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è #metoo #metoomovement #timesup #autism #autismspeaks #tulsa #oklahoma #fashionfotoge #fashionfotog #fashionfotogevita #evita #model #photographer #writer #travelwriter #manager #actor #talent #wildlifephotographer #wildlife #fashionphotographer #runwaycoach #actingcoach #videographer #artdirector #copywriter #graphicdesign #advertising

a legacy
so far removed
one day will be improved
eternal rights
we left behind

i always looked to you
i always looked to you
i always looked to you

on foreign soil
where ageless lovers call
is this your goal
your final needs
where dogs and vultures eat
committed still i turn to go

i put my trust in you
i put my trust in you
in you. in you. in you
put my trust in you, in you

text:
hey trauma, the day we met....
.
i lost every ounce of dignity for myself. i often feel shackled to shame, guilt, self-hate, and fear. when we move from childhood into adulthood there are many roles/identities you dream of stepping into, but ‚Äòsurvivor‚Äô isn‚Äôt one of them! but here i am...an unexpected survivor of abuse.
.
i‚Äôm often told - almost demanded - to get over it or move on. sure, the bruises and bones have healed many times, but mentally i can‚Äôt get over the shame & pain of trauma. i feel nothing except worthless, sad, damaged from the inside out, unrecognizable.
.
for me trauma is this 20ft. wall that surrounds & blocks everything. is this surviving?
......anonymous‚ú®
.
.
.

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

text:
üíÄ ùïπùñéùñåùñçùñôùñíùñÜùñóùñä ùï≠ùñäùñãùñîùñóùñä ùïÆùñçùñóùñéùñòùñôùñíùñÜùñò üíÄ
here's what i was wearing this sunday (dec 23rd 2018) when i was intimidated and verbally abused by a man twice my size for not returning his "merry christmas" or conceding to his demands to explain my alternative holiday & beliefs right there on the dance floor. üî™
i'm a petite creature and i have been physically intimidated by men a lot in my life.  but i think it is really *interesting* that this always seems to happen to me when i am dressed #femme,  glamorous high femme, or sometimes without makeup and therefore i look even younger.  but it  hardly ever happens when i am dressed androgynous,  grungey, or downright boyish.
üíÄ
aesthetics is what i do for a living, and costume is part of who i am,  so i will never stop dressing up... but its sad to me that entitled men see me as an easy target when i look like a bite sized femme. honestly it does make me think twice about wearing stuff like that out... i'm not even talking about revealing or "slutty" clothes,  im talking about projected gender & sexuality identity. üî™
men don't pick fights with me when i "look like a lesbian" only when i "look like a little girl" - what does that tell you about how sick our culture is? üíÄ
i already blocked this man from my account but if he's not signed in he can still see this post... so this i say to him:
‚û°Ô∏èdo not cross my path again. ‚û°Ô∏èdo not underestimate me. ‚û°Ô∏èdo not forget that i am licensed to wield sharp objects. üî™

text:
i like to envision the new year this way, being granted the gift of more time. more opportunities to experience new things, to meet new people, more time to reach your dreams. ..
this time last year i was in so much pain, the nerve pain was overbearing and trying to walk even with the crutches was horrid. i spent my new years eve in hospital trying to get the pain under control... i was alone, crying and wanting to end my life... looking back, i can be proud of how much i got through this year and  it has been a year of big tests and realizations also. ..
i haven't felt so excited about the new year in quite a while. the prospect of what the year will bring feels very positive! i know that shit happens also but i am going to make the best of what the year brings to me üëåüèªüòäüíúüíúüíúüôåüèª #bringon2019 #mentalhealthwarrior #traumasurvivor #healing #recovery #believeinyourself #love #life #youmatter #youcanhealyourlife #strength #support #healingthoughts #surviveandthrive #inspiration #time #gift #positivevibes #mentalhealthreminders #selflovethoughts #wellbeing #mentalwellness #yougotthis #positivereminders #quotetoliveby #metoo #sexualabuse #mentalhealthjourney

text: to those on a similar road..it has been a long road. a slow road. but a road i am glad i stepped on. the road before me is not, by any means, an easy one. but one i face now determined. i am relearning to do and wear what -i- actually, genuinely enjoy. for a very very long time what i "enjoyed" was based on if it made someone else happy or not. but slowly i started to get back to what i genuinly found pleasure in, found comfort in, felt good in. and slowly all the cracked and broken pieces are being forged whole again. in my minds eye it has the appearance of mercury glass. imperfect, but shiny and unique in its beauty. to those finding their feet on the path. keep going!! keep fighting!! you will make it and be far better for it. reclaim your special energy and don't look back!!!üíñüíóüíñ#selflove #selfcare #selfdiscovery #wellbeing #wellness #jusssayin #settingboundariesandfsu #thetruthturnsmeon #boundaries #nocontact #redflags #narcissist #narcissisticabuse #narcissism #metoo #abuse #crazymaking #traumabonding #emotionalabuse #toxicrelationships #survivor #gaslighting #toxicpeople¬† #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolence #believewomen #ifmywoundswerevisible #dontlookback #narcissisticabusesurvivor

text:
repito, la violencia es real.
con #metoo y #miprimeracoso, el mundo se ha enterado pero las mujeres lo hemos sabido siempre: no hay ni una sola que no haya vivido acoso, abuso, violaci√≥n y las cifras oficiales se quedan cortas.
como parteras, vemos mucho que el abuso sexual que las mujeres vivieron resurge en el embarazo, en consultas ginecol√≥gicas, al hacer un tacto en el parto,... el cuerpo no olvida y el nervio pudendo menos.
por eso es tan importante que hagamos todo, todo, todo y m√°s para asegurarnos que las mujeres sepan que ellas son las que tienen el poder en el proceso acompa√±ado por nosotras. ya sea en el parto, en un papanicolau o en la puesta de un diu, como proveedoras debemos darles esa seguridad y confianza a las mujeres - con palabras y actos.
recuerdo el parto de una mujer con antecedentes de abuso que le segu√≠a causando secuelas vaginales. ella tem√≠a que si le hac√≠a un tacto, se tensar√≠a mucho y no se lo podr√≠a hacer. yo le aseguraba que probablemente no ser√≠a necesario y si s√≠, pod√≠amos trabajar muy lentamente, con ella en control siempre. cuando me pidi√≥ un tacto, me pregunt√≥ que si ella se pod√≠a meter mis dedos y as√≠ lo hicimos y fue muy sencillo.
despu√©s del parto vimos que hubo un desgarre que hab√≠a que suturar. me pregunt√≥ que si ella se pod√≠a colocar la anestesia porque la pon√≠a muy nerviosa que yo se la pusiera. y le di la jeringa, gui√© su mano y le se√±al√© donde meter la aguja y la meti√≥ ella.
la atenci√≥n centrada en la mujer es posible, importante y no deber√≠a ser algo que tengamos que negociar. como proveedoras la deber√≠amos ofrecer y practicar siempre. como mujeres no deber√≠amos aceptar menos.
como proveedoras, desgraciadamente tenemos que asumir de todas las mujeres que han vivido alg√∫n tipo de violencia sexual, aunque no lo digan. lo ‚Äúpeor‚Äù que puede pasar es que no lo vivieron y las tratamos bien. lo mejor: apoyar a que puedan resignificar sensaciones y emociones y saberse due√±as de ellas mismas y sus procesos.

text:
ground palm strike ‚úãüèª& ground hammer fist ü§úüèª .
.
.
.
i was doing this ground & pound drill in my workout today (i just love it) but you can definitely apply this for self-defense if needed. .
.
.
i am basically doing the palm strike and hammer fist to a target on the ground. .
.
.
for the ground palm strike i am using the heel of my palm as the surface area (curling my fingers back to get them out of the way).
.
.
.
for the ground hammer fist i am using the side of my fist as a surface area.
.
.
.
both strikes feel solid physically as i can strike harder using these surface areas.
.
.
.
if you practice this, make sure you have a good training pad that can take the impact. a really thick pillow, couch or mattress can also work if you need to get creative.
.
.
.
i also always recommend that anyone incorporating my drills do a few reps slowly and then gradually increase the speed or power to stay safe and prevent injury.
.
.
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
‚Ä¢d o  w h a t  y o u  e n j o y‚Ä¢

i‚Äôve done p90x, insanity, piyo, yoga, zumba, classes at the ymca, and who knows what else.  none of it stuck.

i remember marking the workouts off the calendar included in the program, only to get to the end of the month and have several workouts i needed to make up üôÑi never enjoyed listening to shawn t anyway, so i stopped.

i found my love for backpacking/hiking in 2015 when a friend invited me to join her on the appalachian trail.  it was so rewarding hiking mountains everyday, then being so exhausted in the evening that i often ate my ramen noodle raw with a side of gummy worms. yum üòã i wish i could do that everyday, but unfortunately there‚Äôs a major lack of mountains in northeast ohio.
‚òπÔ∏è
it wasn‚Äôt until 2017 when my best friend invited me to a crossfit class with her.  i‚Äôve been hooked since.  i love the challenge, community, and that everyday is different!  i‚Äôve only done it for a total of 11 months, but it‚Äôs legit the only workout i consistently do and enjoy!
üèãüèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
maybe crossfit isn‚Äôt your thing. that‚Äôs okay! just do something that actually brings you joy because if you love it you will keep doing it! & bless your heart if that‚Äôs running.  that‚Äôs a hard pass for me üôÖüèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

my new life is so much better than my old one. but there was a cost to pay: everything. new friends. a new job. rebuilding my finances. finding a new bar to hangout at. skipping shows.

but that wasn‚Äôt even the hard part. i had to remind myself that my old life was a lie‚Äîat least on my abuser‚Äôs part. all those good times, all the times i thought my abuser might actually love me, i had to remind myself that those weren‚Äôt true. my abuser had an agenda. and that‚Äôs where it cost me. i didn‚Äôt want to believe that.

text:
just ready to get out of the midwest. 
i am a city girl at heart who happens to love hiking and waterfalls, my heart does not belong in tulsa, oklahoma. 
i'm an introverted extrovert who needs time to myself, but gets lonely after so long and needs to talk to human beings. 
i am agnostic at best and i have no place in "the buckle of the bible belt."
i love dressing up, #yoga, #animals, #lgbtq+, #feminism, #equality, #democracy, #metoo, books, and #fundamentalrights.
i am a #vegetarian atm but am working to become #vegan.  i support #crueltyfree and vegan products.
i love the arts. #music, #theatre, #painting, #expression.
i am a published #authorillustrator of a children's book #thezoocrew
right now i am 100% dependant on ss disabilty income and my life savings, my paychecks never make it through the month.
i endure anorexia, depression, anxiety, ptsd, borderline personality disorder, and treatments of #electroconvulsivetherapy.
i believe in a family of choice.  i believe that no one should tell you how to believe.  i believe in rainbows and golden tickets that open up the doors to oppertunity. 
#amda is my golden ticket and my audition is april 7th :)

text:
let's talk about multiple oppressions. inspired by @dev.manning. ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
{quick trigger warning- mentions of slurs (never said explicitly), sexual assault, and gender dysphoria.}
i am a typically non passing, fem/andro expressing trans masc person who is also queer, neurodivergent, and a sexual assault survivor. there is not a minute that goes by which i do not have to be conscious of my identities. whether it is walking home and hearing slurs/cat calls (which i still get for some reason??), my mental health impacting my interactions with others and myself, or living with the worry of what the next person i meet might say. 
each form of oppression impacts the others. and many times i find them to be inseparable when i try to analyze them as individuals. 
the world around me sends clear messages that who i am is an unwelcome oddity. that i as a trans person am disgusting and that i can never live up to what it means to be cis in society. that i as a sexual assault survivor am lying, stretching the truth, or not getting over my traumas fast enough. that i as a neurodivergent person am "crazy", unlovable and irrational. 
i am working to unlearn these internalized messages because i know that i am not alone in experiencing them. i am working to understand the privileges i do have (i am able bodied, middle class, and white). it can be east to forget our privileges when we have multiple oppressed identities, but from my experience it is extremely important to understand your privilege and leverage it where you can. ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
photographer-@b.martin ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

because that‚Äôs the only way we will get equality.

text:
i know there is a genuine confusion and awkwardness about how to approach someone you like.
it's because nobody talks to us about these things.
but keep these things in mind
1) don't always expect a response.
2) the person isn't entitled to talk to you. respect that boundary.
3)if they're interested, they'll respond.read the body language
4) if they're closed and reserved, try and stop the conversation. they're probably getting freaked out
5) if you're complimenting, choose your words carefully.

you don't know anyone's past and why they might be scared or reserved. 
you don't know how new people preceive you. be careful

text:
so, you and your partner(s) are at the stage in your relationship where you want to get physically intimate.
or you're at a club where the wine is flowing, music is pounding, eyes match,  chemistry is in the air and you're about to get lucky!

but you know that voice in your head that's wondering if it's safe? listen to it! this is an idiot proof guide to make sure you don't walk away from the bed with more than just passionate memories.

step 1 is consent. in this age, it's extremely important to make sure that everyone involved agrees to have sex. no means no! 
be clear in what you are proposing. nothing is sexier than standing for your conviction and being confident.
be safe, be sober, be clear!

check out our other posts for steps 2 and 3 for the rest of the guide 
thanks as well to @doc.shail for helping compile this guide.

text:
using this yummy olive oil today! was a gift from my management team, i am sure everyone else on my team got wine. i used to get wine as well, often times as a gift for winning a contest or something like that and often around the holidays. 
it was hard to be honest about it in the beginning but now it's not an issue and they know i prefer fancy olive oil and have made sure our events have non alcoholic beer for me üíì honesty has been the only way for me to succeed while staying sober 
don't believe the narrative that recovery is painful and impossible to accomplish in corporate america. there are so many people who told me my career would be over and i would not be able to maintain long term sobriety in technology sales and it's simply not true.  it's so crazy to me now that i felt the same way, i thought it was impossible for years. but i got help for myself and implemented my sobriety while continuing my challenging career because of the lessons i learned in treatment. i didn't try to do it on my own because i don't believe in that approach about anything in life. i get help from professionals in all areas of my life and why would sobriety be any different? i went to aa in the beginning but felt like it was just incredibly ineffective for the time commitment and didn't provide much in terms of wellness. i need more than just a support group.  i needed individual treatment and my insurance benefits covered holistic treatment so there was no reason not to use the coverage i am entitled to. it was only after arriving in rehab that i learned how rare i was... only 8 percent of employers even have anyone using their benefits for recovery üò• the stigma attached to addiction is so strong we hide and it gets worse. 
treatment is more effective when it's given earlier in the progression of the issue. don't let the stigma stop you from living your best life!

text:
what is trauma-focused therapy? this is also known as trauma-informed care (tic). tic is not about specific therapeutic techniques.  it is an overall approach, a philosophy of providing care. 
addresses the specific emotional and mental health needs of those who are struggling to overcome the effects of traumatic experiences. 
key principles of tic: 
1.a safe therapeutic environment is essential to aid in recovery. 
2.trauma-related symptoms and behaviors originate from adapting to traumatic experiences. 
3. recovery from trauma is identified as a goal in treatment. 
4. resiliency and trauma-resistant skills training are part of treatment. 
5. trauma-informed care includes a focus on strengths rather than pathology. 
6. trauma recovery is a collaborative effort between therapist and client
.

a little boy sexually molested for several years. life repeatedly showed and reaffirmed he wasn‚Äôt wanted or loved by anyone even through adulthood. no one would listen. what wouldn‚Äôt we do for love, to feel we belonged and wanted?  what wouldn‚Äôt we do to stop the pain? how do you feel about this little boy?  too often he held a cold black steel muzzle of a gun on the temple or mouth, told lies, deceptions, infidelities, stuff unfathomable. [. ]
how would you feel if the little boy found love, attention, and all the worlds blessings and is now living his purpose, freely, happily, and with all the love he could ever want and also chooses to share his secrets of a turned around life with anyone who would listen.
[. ]
would you listen?  would you want to know more?
[. ]
by the way, the little boy was me, the new man is also me. perfectly imperfect.
[. ]

.

aloe vera contains proteolytic enzymes, which help heal and repair the damaged cells in your scalp. this improves the health of the hair follicles and indirectly boosts healthy and faster hair growth.

not only does the proteolytic enzyme help heal the scalp, but it also helps stimulate dormant hair follicles, promoting hair regrowth.

it also helps curb hair fall and controls hair shedding, ensuring that your hair remains thick and voluminous.

it has anti-inflammatory properties that help soothe your scalp of irritation and aggravation.

its antifungal and antiviral properties to treat dandruff and flaking.

aloe vera‚Äôs high content of protein, vitamins, and minerals help it nourish your follicles and hair efficiently.

the moisture content of aloe vera helps condition your hair, locking in nutrients and hydration

text:
20 years ago i quit architecture school after experiencing alienation & culture shock at @sciarc. i left the field but didn‚Äôt give up hope on reforms. i‚Äôm now part of reform efforts. i joined the @arch_lobby @archlobby.la, #losangeles chapter.

read our #manifesto üåπ

we are precarious workers. these are our demands:

1) enforce labor laws that prohibit unpaid internships, unpaid overtime; refuse unpaid competitions.

2) reject fees based on percentage of construction or hourly fees and instead calculate value based on the money we save our clients, or gain them.

3) stop peddling a product‚Äîbuildings‚Äîand focus on the unique value architects help realize through spatial services.

4) enforce wage transparency across the discipline.

5) establish a union for architects, designers, academics and interns in architecture and design.

6) demystify the architect as solo creative genius; no honors for architects who don‚Äôt acknowledge their staff.

7) licensure upon completion of degree.

8) change professional architecture organizations to advocate for the living conditions of architects.

9) support research about professional labor rights in architecture.

10) implement democratic alternatives to the free market system of development.

the architecture lobby, inc. is an organization of architectural #workers advocating for the value of #architecture in the general public and for architectural work within the discipline. it believes that the work architects do‚Äîaesthetic, technical, social, organizational, environmental, administrative, fiduciary‚Äîneeds structural change to be more rewarding and more socially relevant. as long as architecture tolerates abusive practices in the office and the construction site, it cannot insist on its role in and for the public good.
name: Jonathan Pacheco Bell, MA+MLIS

text:
i was frozen in my mind & heart about drawing illustrations for a children‚Äôs series i‚Äôm dreaming of. 
i‚Äôd tell myself, ‚Äúyou can only be an abstract artist.‚Äù
then my husband asked me a question that he already knew the answer to, ‚Äúwhat was your dream when you went to college? what did you study & why?‚Äù
i immediately got tears in my eyes. i answered, ‚Äúi was an art major/film minor.‚Äù
you see, i wanted to be an animator.
i wanted to work for disney or warner bros! 
except trauma started speaking to that dream. my choices took a devastating turn where i stepped into the sex industry & my life & dreams unraveled. 
years later, healing began. i began painting abstract & expressing my heart through paint. abstract felt safer to me. yet always afraid to draw. and if i tried, everything i did i saw as crap. junk. horrible art! 
so when bob asked me,
‚Äúwhat was your childhood dream when you went to college? what did you study & why?‚Äù
i answered in a new way...because of all of the healing i have received in the last couple of years, trauma didn‚Äôt get to answer the question this time. 
i am an artist. i can sketch. i can learn to illustrate. i am not afraid to try. 
and that longing and dream inside of me feels just as big as when i was younger & i believed i could do anything! 
what i‚Äôm learning...
it‚Äôs ok to renew a dream. 
trauma & abuse don‚Äôt get to dictate my life. 
it‚Äôs hard work healing from a lifetime of traumas. so never quit! 
art is hard work (and most all things you don‚Äôt know, are) & i will practice because it‚Äôs something i love deeply! 
happy new year friends! ‚ù§Ô∏è

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i‚Äôve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i‚Äôm about to go back, knowing what i know, and we‚Äôre about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump‚Äôs election, trumpeted the return of their ‚Äúpopulist hero‚Äù on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication‚Äôs announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there‚Äôs any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i‚Äôm leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents ‚Äì on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: i feel strongly enough about this news story to remind everyone that women‚Äôs rights also mean the right and the need to remind our daughters to be careful about what images they post of themselves and where they post them. beauty is often best when its subtle. as moms we must teach them to be cautious, to use the buddy system, to be aware of their surroundings, to avoid putting themselves in dangerous situations. lets make #metoo also #meownself meaning we think about protecting ourselves before bad things happen. #meownself please this holiday season encourage your daughters to be their own #meownself and take all precautionary measures they can.

text:
i really debated sharing this, but i also really wanted to leave this portion of my pain in 2018. i go through large spurts of growth and healing only to find myself still affected by my past every now and again. i know recovery isn‚Äôt linear, but it feels defeating sometimes. while i can‚Äôt guarantee this will stay in 2018, this is my effort to make it that way.
a few weeks ago my cousin shared with me that a friend of hers filed a no-contact order to keep an abusive ex out of her life, and she was met with support and encouragement from not only her friends and community, but the local pd as well. it made my heart so happy.
in the fall of 2015, i called the cops on my ex-husband one night. partly because he had just had one of his huge, out-of-proportion violent rages, and partly because he took to locking himself in his vehicle to drink and i couldn‚Äôt, no matter how much i was hurting, turn a blind eye with a good conscious.
however, when the cops arrived, i was the culprit. i was the reason behind my ex-husbands behavior. it didn‚Äôt matter how many months of emotional, mental, physical abuse and infidelity i put up with, i was the cause. it didn‚Äôt matter that he was a grown adult making his own decisions and choosing his behaviors. and i saw it, and heard it, when the cop taking my statement smiled and condescendingly said, ‚Äúyou know, if you had done something about this sooner, he wouldn‚Äôt be in this state tonight.‚Äù
if >i< had done something sooner? the months of pleading for him to get help? to see a therapist? the multiple times he got within centimeters of my face, threatening me if i told his superiors or did anything that might affect his employment? i was even afraid to drive myself to the hospital the night i tried to end my life for fear of retribution if word got out to his peers and superiors.
you mean every night he made the decision, as a full-grown 30-year-old man, to drink? to become emotionally manipulative and abusive?
and >i< should have done something about it sooner to positively affect him? i, as many women in my culture growing up in the valley, put the entire weight of my marriage on my shoulders. i blamed myself for every failing.
name: Rebecca Izaguirre

text:
i‚Äôve spent a lot of today processing the incredible experience i had yesterday, supporting this amazing cause. this isn‚Äôt meant to be a boastful post at all about how i spent my christmas.. although i went excitedly along to teach yoga, there was just a bit of that in the end, and my learnings were not the shape making on the mat in the way that i envisaged. i was touched by the many people i came into contact with and really blown away that 99% of the residents in the centre i volunteered in were men. at the time i was really shocked by this, but thinking about it more i guess it‚Äôs no surprise in some ways. more and more statistics show that male suicide is on the rise... and although #metoo has been so important and totally can‚Äôt be ignored, the anger around this seems to have somehow overshadowed the many other good people out there, men and women alike. i came away feeling like some important healing and deeper bridge building still needs to happen between men and women. it seems that so much is still misunderstood about the needs and vulnerabilities of both sexes and how we can now truly meet each other on a more human level and not based on what is somehow expected by society or conditioning. it really was food for thought for me, and such an eye opening experience. 
today i‚Äôm feeling grateful not just for the roof over my head, and the many blessings in my life but the connections i have with both the men  and women, all those close, and the amazing healers, yoga teachers, therapists, and other amazing creatives of all kinds who step out in the world and are trying to help build these bridges, supporting a world where we can all just meet each other, and live a life filled with wholeness and love and really be met as we are. feels like something i want to carry with me, as i leave this year and step into a new one. not just in terms of what i offer out to others in my creativity but also how open hearted i want to be and really be grateful for each day and grab life, as well as really connect and love  the people i‚Äôm fortunate enough to share my life with ‚ù§Ô∏èüôèüèº‚ù§Ô∏è
name: Charlotte Nolan

why me, was a question that i often asked myself growing up as a hopeless sexually abused child.

i didn‚Äôt have a relationship with the lord then, and yet even now as a believer i still ask, why me. 
but this time it‚Äôs different.

i no longer ask the lord why me with a bitter, angry, sad, frustrated, heart, but with a heart of humility that seeks to know how god wants to use me and my sexual abuse past to help point others to christ and build his kingdom.

realizing and embracing the fact that the evil of sexual abuse that happened to me was all apart of god‚Äôs sovereign plan, i no longer dwell on my suffering, sorrow, and self-pity.

instead i choose to hope in and trust god, even if i don‚Äôt fully understand his plan or purpose, because his ways are higher than mine and his thoughts are higher than mine,isaiah 55:8-9.

text:
to the girl from the city,

i'm reena. i'm 16 years old and i too have the same dreams and aspirations just like you. but i know being a girl is not easy. people judge you everyday, everytime. being uneducated, living in an unknown village from bengal i don't know how to write letters or read the news. my neighbor has a radio which is turned on throughout the day. i've heard a lot of stories about the women being raped in the clubs. the skirts, the short dresses always become the victims. living in a well educated society you people started a #metoo movement recently exposing the wrongs done to you.
-
let me tell you. i also have a story to share. we don't have any social media or any mode of communicating the world. we don't get the opportunity to share our stories instead we need to hide them. so let me speak out. let me tell you its not only the skirts that become the victims of rape but the burkhas and salwar kameez all fall in the list. -

a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he‚Äôs the only straight man i‚Äôve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‚Äòugh. totally ugly‚Äô to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it‚Äôs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don‚Äôt necessarily know it‚Äôs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it‚Äôs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you‚Äôre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people‚Äôs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn‚Äôt have seen, and couldn‚Äôt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, ‚Äúwould work for anyone‚Äù. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they‚Äôre mercenaries. they‚Äôll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it‚Äôs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing ‚Äì at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public ‚Äì our intimate family connections, our ‚Äúlikes‚Äù, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that‚Äôs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‚Äòugh. totally ugly‚Äô to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it‚Äôs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don‚Äôt necessarily know it‚Äôs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it‚Äôs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you‚Äôre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people‚Äôs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn‚Äôt have seen, and couldn‚Äôt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, ‚Äúwould work for anyone‚Äù. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they‚Äôre mercenaries. they‚Äôll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it‚Äôs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing ‚Äì at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public ‚Äì our intimate family connections, our ‚Äúlikes‚Äù, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that‚Äôs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
habari gani? umoja! to strive for and maintain unity in the family, community, nation and race.
unity doesn't mean blind loyalty. in contrast, umoja challenges us to hold one another accountable, to see ourselves in our brothers and sisters, and ultimately to understand that our fates are intertwined.
umoja fully recognizes intersectionality and says that the individual cannot be free unless the group is free. i say this in the wake of the #metoo moment this year. how many black women remained silent to protect black men who were their abusers? i honor and uplift all the black women who did speak up. i honor and uplift the black woman, tarana burke, who started the #metoo movement because sexual violence against black women is under-reported and overlooked. umoja means we cannot deal with just one issue - racism or sexism or whatever else. umoja requires an "and".
#umoja #kwanzaa #happykwanzaa #intersectionality #blackwomen #unity

happy boxing day #frotribe. .
.
i'm sure we're all busy packing on the holiday calories. i know i am.. üòÅüòÅüòÅ
.
.

so due to the very very dry and cold weather, i had to make aloe vera juice to be used as my daily hair spritz. all i added to it was a few drops of my hair growth elixir.  so perfect! ü§óü§ó. .
.

aloe vera is very very effective in maintaining a moisturized hair and preventing dryness and itchy scalp. .
.
so picture 1 is the freshly cut aloe vera leaves. make sure to use the big mature and juicy ones. .
.
picture 2 is the extracted gel which i got by using a sharp knife to gently slice off the green parts of the leave. the gel is housed in the center of the leaves. .
.
picture 3 is the final product which is the aloe vera juice. i got this by blending the extracted gel with about a cup of water which i then sieved using a cheese cloth to extract the pulp. .
voila!  the aloe vera juice is ready. .
simple right? .
i transferred it to my spray bottle and added a few drops of @fro_guard hair growth elixir. .
.
.
my next post will be on the benefits of aloe vera to the hair. .
.
who else loves using aloe vera? üôã

text:
we are pleased to announce our first national essay writing competition, that is a small step in our endeavour to create social awareness and a sense of social responsibility in the youth citizens of our country.
the above stated competition will be adjudged by jury consisting of law faculty from 5 prestigious law colleges. 
the topics for the competition are:
*failure of legal machinery & emergence of #metoo moment *transformative constitutionalism and subrimala judgement
*sustainable development in india & around the world.

the last date of submission of essays is 31st of january, and the registration shall be completed by 20th january.

for registration the candidates need to fill the googleform provided in the given link:
https://goo.gl/forms/th7knjakch6s9jnj2 
the registration fee is rs 250 
winning prize is rs 5100 along with rs 2100 for runner-up, every participant will be advanced an e-certificate under the banner of "social-curator"
for any further queries contact at:
ph:9780361242, 7973767217
email:socialcurator4@gmail.com

text:
an argument against those who claim that women dressed scantily deserve to get raped. to begin with, no one- man or woman ‚Äúdeserves to get raped‚Äù; irrespective of how he or she is dressed. the point i was making through this photograph: indian women typically wear the ‚Äúsaree‚Äù. it is normally 27 feet long and is draped around the woman‚Äôs body. with the alarming incidents of rape across india, one certainly cannot use the rationale that the woman was scantily dressed.
so the onus for rape and sexual molestations lies on the indian man. #incredibleindia #metoo #indianwedding #women #womenempowerment #womensfashion #indian #rapevictim #rapememes #rapeculture #mumbai #vogueindia #indiavogue #mumbai_uncensored #mumbaifashionblogger #designersareemumbai #mumbaigirls #modelsindia #indiamodels #girls #indiaphotoproject
